Package WYSIWYM.model

Interface Summary
DatatypeNode DatatypeNode is an interface for nodes that contain some datatype (instead of corresponding to an individual)
TreeComponent TreeComponent is an interface for components of trees (nodes and edges).
 

Class Summary
Anchor Anchor represents the expansion points in the feedback text.
ContentPlan ContentPlan represents a conceptual plan of the feedback text and holds DependencyTrees.
DependencyTree DependencyTree represents one sentence in the text plan.
DTEdge DTEdge is an edge in a Dependency Tree.
DTNode  
Edge Edge is an interface for tree edges.
FeedbackText FeedbackText holds the text (consisting of AnchorStrings) that the user sees and edits.
Graph Graph is an abstract superclass for graph structures (such as SemanticGraph and DependencyTree)
Morph Morph holds the morphological information of a DTNode
Node Node is an interface for tree nodes
QueryEdge QueryEdge in an edge in the QueryGraph.
QueryGraph QuerycGraph holds the query the user is building.
QueryNode QueryNode is a node in the QueryGraph.
QueryPlan QueryPlan represents a conceptual plan of the query.
QueryResultAnchor QueryResultAnchor is a placeholder anchor, that signals the interface that this phrase should be marked as an anchor (user can click it to see full description of corresponding object).
QueryResultGraph QueryResultGraph contains information about the matches of a particular query.
QueryResultPlan TextPlan represents a conceptual plan of the feedback text and holds DependencyTrees.
QueryValue Contains the value(s) of a datatype query node, and their comparators and boolean operators
QueryValueNode QueryValueNode is a node in the QueryGraph that contains a datatype value.
RealiseEdgeComparator Compares two SGEdges WITH THE SAME LABEL by comparing the realise numbers, which represent the order in which identical edges must be added.
SemanticGraph SemanticGraph holds the metadata structure/query the user is building.
SequenceEdgeComparator Compares two SGEdges with respect to seniority, by comparing the sequence numbers, which represent the order in which edges are attached to enable undo.
SGAbstractNode SGAbstractNode is a SGStringNode that contains an abstract (a large piece of text).
SGAddressNode  
SGBooleanNode SGBooleanNode is a SGNode and DatatypeNode that contains a boolean value.
SGDateNode SGDateNode is a SGNode that instead of a String has a vague date.
SGDoubleNode SGNumberNode is a SGNode that instead of a String has a float.
SGEdge SGEdge is an edge in the Semantic Graph.
SGIntNode SGNumberNode is a SGNode that contains a float value.
SGNode SGNode is a node in the Semantic Graph.
SGStringNode SGStringNode is a SGNode that contains a String datatype
SummationAnchor SummationAnchor signals that a sequence of >3 edges have been summarised in a list.
TemplateAnchor TemplateAnchor is an anchor for the templates used in creating new lexicon entries
TextPlan TextPlan represents a conceptual plan of the feedback text and holds DependencyTrees.
